# EasyPanel Configuration
# This file helps configure the project deployment on EasyPanel

## Services Configuration

### 1. MySQL Database
# Service Name: pulse-blast-db
# Type: MySQL 8.0
# Database Name: pulse_blast
# Username: pulse_user
# Password: <generate-strong-password>

### 2. Backend API (Node.js)
# Service Name: pulse-blast-api
# Type: App
# Source: Git Repository
# Build Method: Nixpacks
# Build Path: /backend
# Port: 3001
# Environment Variables:
#   DB_HOST=pulse-blast-db
#   DB_USER=pulse_user
#   DB_PASSWORD=<mysql-password>
#   DB_NAME=pulse_blast
#   DB_PORT=3306
#   JWT_SECRET=<generate-random-32-byte-hex>
#   PORT=3001
#   NODE_ENV=production
#   FRONTEND_URL=https://<your-frontend-domain>

### 3. Frontend (React)
# Service Name: pulse-blast-frontend
# Type: App
# Source: Git Repository
# Build Method: Nixpacks
# Build Path: / (root)
# Port: 3000
# Environment Variables:
#   VITE_API_URL=https://<your-backend-domain>/api

## Database Schema Setup
# After creating MySQL service:
# 1. Access phpMyAdmin or MySQL CLI
# 2. Run the SQL from: backend/database/schema.sql

## Domain Configuration
# Backend: api.yourdomain.com -> pulse-blast-api:3001
# Frontend: yourdomain.com -> pulse-blast-frontend:3000

## Auto-Deploy
# Push to main branch triggers automatic deployment
